&lt;p&gt;Are you a qualified registered nurse, looking for a rewarding career within a 5-19 Public Health School Nursing team who strives to make a difference on the health outcomes of children and young people living in Derbyshire?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, this opportunity is for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have two part time posts for community staff nurses in the Amber Valley locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will require knowledge of the current public health agenda, in particular the Healthy Child Programme. As a community staff nurse in the school nursing team you will work under the supervision of a School Nurse Specialist Community Public Health Practitioner (SCPHN) and alongside other Community Staff Nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carla Dormon, Locality Manager, carladormon@nhs.net, 07776 485989&lt;/p&gt;
